description: Dark horse Seize the Grey galloped to a Preakness Stakes victory in Baltimore on Saturday, denying Mystik Dan a place in history and delivering another garland of Black-Eyed Susans to legendary trainer D. Wayne Lukas.
title: Seize the Grey wins the Preakness Stakes, ruining Mystik Dan’s Triple Crown odds

description: Preakness favorite Muth has been ruled out of the race after spiking a fever.
title: Mystik Dan enters the Preakness Stakes as the favorite after winning Kentucky Derby

description: CAIRO/JERUSALEM — Israeli troops and tanks pushed on Saturday into parts of a congested northern Gaza Strip district that they had previously skirted in the more than seven-month-old war, killing and wounding dozens of Palestinians, medics and residents said.
title: Israel recovers another slain hostage; pushes into new parts of northern Gaza

description: The city of Houston on Saturday opened new distribution centers to give out water as around 500,000 customers remained without power following severe storms blamed in the deaths of seven people in the region.
title: Houston distributes water as more than 500,000 remain without power after devastating storms

description: A group of former military trauma surgeons are calling for first responders to carry whole blood on rescue vehicles to help save bleeding patients. NBC News' Cynthia McFadden reports on the small number of communities already seeing life-saving results.
title: How ex-military surgeons are pushing for laws allowing ambulances to carry blood

description: After a semester marked by sweeping protests on college campuses across the nation that raised questions about freedom of speech, how universities confront allegations of antisemitism and Islamophobia and how they invest, some students who experienced the demonstrations say they have been left disappointed by how their universities responded.
title: College students who protested and those who didn't share in disappointment at response from schools

description: A movement to revolutionize the treatment of trauma patients in the U.S. can be traced to an infamous battle fought in East Africa more than 30 years ago.
title: Ex-military surgeons embrace new mission: stop Americans from bleeding to death

description: The hottest ticket in New York City is Trump's hush money trial and some are willing to pay big to get to see testimony from Stormy Daniels, Michael Cohen, and more.
title: Trump's hush money trial makes big money for professional line-standers

description: This weekend, President Joe Biden will hold events in cities like Detroit, where Black turnout is critical to efforts in two of the closest battleground states.
title: Amid signs of waning enthusiasm, Biden reaches out to Black voters

description: Canadian teenager Jason Zhao explains his idea of launching a small rocket that will launch a drone upon landing in order to more quickly monitor the growth of wildfires.
title: 17-year-old works to detect wildfires with rocket and drone system
